ormal; line-height: 22.3999996185303px; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: #ffffff;\">, the assignment statement (or expression) is a fundamental construct.</span></p>',0,NULL,'2015-05-08 07:08:56','2015-05-08 07:08:56',177,NULL),(27,160,'my first island assignment',NULL,'<p>One can go snorkeling at Elephant Beach at Havelock Island. It is one of the most preferred snorkeling destinations after Jolly Bouy island in Port Blair</p>',1,NULL,'2015-05-08 07:48:38','2015-05-08 07:48:49',221,NULL),(28,162,'Rshi Assignment submission',NULL,'<p>Rshi Assignment submission</p>',1,NULL,'2015-05-08 08:54:23','2015-05-08 08:57:43',229,NULL),(29,167,'Rishi Assignment Submission',NULL,'<p>Rishi Assignment Submission</p>',1,NULL,'2015-05-08 09:46:22','2015-05-08 09:47:54',242,NULL),(30,130,'Spray Artist Painting Walls of Construction Site',NULL,'<p>The city of Z&uuml;rich decided to let a known artist paint the wall of a construction site to let passerby enjoy some art.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;I tried to make some dynamic photography, although it was not really easy since spray painting is a relatively slow process and require a lot of thinking and working. I went there two times (and plan to go back next week) to try to get some ideas on what kind of images I could get in such a situation.<br />The weather was good, with harsh light and blue skies.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;I tried to capture feelings like: concentration, hard work, improvisation, energy and power. I also tried to give some context (it was painted on a street and not in a studio), and tried some different angle to add some movements to the images (otherwise static).</p>',1,NULL,'2015-05-12 08:33:19','2015-05-12 14:00:14',163,NULL),(31,130,'Graffiti Art - Different views',NULL,'<p>Hi David,</p>\r\n<p>I came back another time and applied what we discussed (small things, adding context). I tried to understand what \"context\" is in this case. My conclusions are that context here is: the street, the long wall, the fact that the artists are working while people are walking by, the sun and heat, the use of specific artistic material (spray so masks are necessary). So I tried &nbsp;to include as much as I could, in the best way possible, of those elements. Trying at the same time to transmit some feelings to the viewer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In addition I tried to pay attention to all small things that you mentioned in your previos comments. I may have missed some (I hope not).</p>\r\n<p>I have other images that I like, but I tried to select the best ones (I am not the best or most experienced picture editor :-) ). But I did\'t want to include too many images :-)&nbsp;</p>',1,NULL,'2015-05-20 15:41:22','2015-05-20 16:19:50',164,NULL),(32,170,'Assignment #2 - Outdoors/manual/ISO 400',NULL,'<p><strong>Created by Suzette Nguyen on May 19, 2015 03:49 - Marked as complete - 3 attachments</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hi David,</p>\r\n<p>I\'m submitting (3) pictures today - is that ok to submit other pictures later for the assignment?</p>\r\n<p>My friend and I made a trip to the San Diego Velodrome this last weekend to snap pictures. We went during peak sun times so the light was really bright. While I did my best to stay at ISO 400, I found that I need to lower the ISO to 100 to capture any pictures with blur.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I don\'t think I\'m going at ideal times because I\'m usually out around peak sun but I don\'t know - thoughts about what time of day to take pictures for the assignment?</p>\r\n<p>Well, as always, your feedback is welcome and appreciated.</p>\r\n<p>Suzette&nbsp;</p>',1,NULL,'2015-05-21 05:48:50','2015-05-21 05:55:25',252,NULL),(33,170,'Assignment #1: Digital Basics - (5) photos',NULL,'<p><strong>Created by Suzette Nguyen on March 02, 2015 00:39 - Marked as complete - 6 attachments</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hello David,</p>\r\n<p>I finally got around to picking up my camera, and had the opportunity to practice and shoot for my first assignment in Anza-Borrego Springs yesterday. I did most of what you asked for but I think my understanding about shooting in Shutter mode is shakier than in Aperture mode.</p>\r\n<p>I look forward to your feedback.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p> Thank you in advance. Suzette&nbsp;</p>',1,NULL,'2015-05-21 13:17:26','2015-05-21 14:04:43',251,NULL),(34,159,'Assignment 1- Understanding my visual style and Draft 1 Positioning Statement',NULL,'<p><strong>Created by Reef Fakhoury on May 19, 2015 11:25 - Marked as complete - 0 attachments</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hello Meeta,</p>\r\n<p>I have been working hard on this assignment. I have created 4 public boards split into the 4 categories we agreed on and compiled shots that I felt I connected with and aspire to be able to capture soon.</p>\r\n<p>I have Also created 5 secret boards with my photographs split into the categories we agreed on, plus an additional \"breakfast\" category. I felt perhaps this needed its own category or subcategory under appetizers and mains (let me know what you think). The boards with my photos are marked as secret and I invited you to access these 5 boards (I used&nbsp;meeta@meetakwolff.com as the email address to reach you. Please confirm you got the invites and can access the boards).</p>\r\n<p>Regarding what I found out about my style from the general boards, please see below my analysis:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">I connect most with very \'styled\' story telling images which incorporate the ingredients and suitable props. <br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">The theme of the dish, ingredient or drink is usually evident by the way the styling is done (for example summer dish, christmas dish, etc). The theme is also usually evident in the location in which the image is taken</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Side lighting is my prefered lighting (my eye is usually drawn to shots that are side lit more so than back lit)</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">45 degree angle is my preferred angle and I relate to food shots taken from this angle (seemingly) more than other angles</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Close up shots (tight) are a preference it seems</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Dark backdrops, boards and props with a well lit subject seems to be recurrent in my selection</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Action shots are very appealing as well (drinks poured, sugar dusted, sauce drizzled, etc)</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Harmonious colors are appealing to my eye more than contrasting or complimentary colors apparently</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>I want to highlight that the way I went about this is by selecting all images without thinking about why I am drawn to them. Only after I felt I had sufficient inspiration shots in each category, I studied the images and drew the above conclusions about my taste. Very insightful excersise! Thank you :)</p>\r\n<p>Finally when it comes to my shots in the secret boards, I feel, to say the least, I have a loooong way to go :(</p>\r\n<p>Now onto my Positioning Statement, Please see below what I came up with after studying loads of my favorite bloggers/ photographers \"About Me\" pages. Please note that I related with concise, humble and up to a certain extent casual style (but not too casual that its almost conversational). Also, please note that this is incomplete as I didn\'t know how to end it! I havent had any hands on experience with clients so I couldn\'t say some thing like \"and this is where I am today, i have worked with X, Y and Z\" to end it... here goes:</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">With a previous life in advertising, public relations and hospitality marketing, I have had over 10 years to develop an eye and a passion for compelling visuals that tell a story. My name is Reef, and I am a freelance photographer based in Copenhagen, Denmark, specializing in food and beverage photography.</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">I developed my appreciation and love for this craft while working as the marketing manager for a luxury hotel chain in Dubai. During that time I had the opportunity to work with a number of great photographers and visual artists in an &lsquo;art director&rsquo; capacity, and just about four years into that, I decided to take the plunge and pursue my passion for photography from behind the lens. I started off working as an assistant to an established food photographer, and additionally to one of the few food stylist in Dubai, with the aim of learning as much as possible on both fronts.</span></p>',1,NULL,'2015-05-22 06:22:25','2015-05-22 06:35:52',215,NULL);
