r-cream-waffles.html\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">http://www.whatsforlunchhoney.net/2011/03/rmmevafler-norwegian-sour-cream-waffles.html</span></a></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Granola bars: <a href=\"http://www.whatsforlunchhoney.net/2011/03/rmmevafler-norwegian-sour-cream-waffles.html\">http://www.whatsforlunchhoney.net/2011/03/rmmevafler-norwegian-sour-cream-waffles.html</a></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">I hope you have a good time with this assignment. I suggest a Skype meeting say in 2 weeks time say on the 3rd June to discuss any issues, progress etc. </span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">But please do not hesitate to get a hold of me here / email and we can discuss things further. </span><br /><br /></span><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">xo</span></span><strong><em><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><br /></span></em></strong></p>',17,7,NULL,'2015-04-09 16:07:12','2015-05-21 07:24:58'),(120,213,'Step 3','','<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong><em>TO BE ANNOUNCED</em></strong></span></p>',17,7,NULL,'2015-04-09 16:26:59','2015-05-08 07:25:44'),(121,214,'Step 4','','<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><em><strong>TO BE ANNOUNCED</strong></em></span></p>',17,7,NULL,'2015-04-10 12:33:05','2015-05-08 07:26:26'),(122,215,'Step 5','','<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong><em>TO BE ANNOUNCED</em></strong></span></p>',17,7,NULL,'2015-04-10 12:35:38','2015-05-08 07:27:00'),(123,216,'Step 6','','<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><em><strong>TO BE ANNOUNCED</strong></em></span></p>',15,7,NULL,'2015-04-10 12:40:05','2015-05-08 07:27:32'),(124,217,'Selecting Your Assignment','','<p>For this first assignment, I would like you to consider just what photo assignment you might give yourself.&nbsp; Keep in mind the criteria we\'ve discussed and the fact that you will have just four weeks to deadline.&nbsp; Briefly describe your assignment and create a sketchpad similar to the one presented in the lesson.&nbsp; It doesn\'t have to be technically perfect, just snapshots of the subject and/ or situation you will be covering.&nbsp; Choose six images from this collection and upload them to the TCI site.&nbsp; Have fun jumping in and getting started!</p>',7,0,NULL,'2015-04-13 08:52:42','2015-04-13 08:52:42'),(125,218,'Planning Your Project','','<p>Now take a step further into YOUR chosen assignment by focusing on the types of storytelling shots described above.&nbsp; Once you\'ve practiced each and feel comfortable making all, upload your two strongest images from each of the three shot categories - overview / scene-setting, middle-distance shot and close-up / detail shot - <strong>6 photographs in all</strong>.&nbsp; Have fun!&nbsp;</p>',18,7,NULL,'2015-04-13 09:48:33','2015-04-13 09:50:08'),(126,219,'Capturing the Images','','<p>There comes a point during a self-assignment where you need to put all of your planning and decision-making into practice in order to reach the deadline you\'ve set for yourself.&nbsp; In this case, it\'s the end of this course.&nbsp; Knowing now the kinds of images that will tell your chosen story, go out and complete your coverage, filling in any gaps in visual information and categories of images you will need to make and edit your final layout.&nbsp; As I have done in this week\'s lesson, upload to the TCI website, four to five images from each photo cateogory (i.e. scene-setting / overview, middle-distance and close-up / detail shot) that you will include for a final edit of your self-assignment - <strong>12 - 15 </strong>of your strongest images in terms of <em>style</em> and <em>content</em>.&nbsp; Have fun!</p>',18,7,NULL,'2015-04-13 13:22:26','2015-04-13 13:24:23'),(127,220,'Toning the Final Layout','','<p>If self-assigned photo coverage is well \"researched\" using a visual \"sketchbook\" design, a solid plan of just how the shoot will proceed is devised and it all is done with a reasonable degree of adaptability and flexibility, the result will be a stunning and strong collection of photos that can then be edited down to a tight and effective lfinal photo layout.&nbsp; For this final assignment I want you to do just that.&nbsp; Take your 12-15 photographs submitted for the third week\'s assignment and create your final <strong>8-photo</strong>, self-assigned story.&nbsp; Please also include a brief explanation of why you chose the images you did for your final selection and do so according to shot category (i.e. scene-setting / overview shot, middle-distance shots and close-ups).&nbsp; Consider your final choices carefully, keeping in mind the four characteristics of a good, strong photograph - 1) great light (or as close to it as possible); 2) great color; 3) interesting composition (Rule-of-Thirds is a good guideline for this); and 4) a marked \"sense of moment\" (i.e. something happening action-wise or beyond the ordinary in the photo).&nbsp; Think eye-catching opener, strong body of your story to hold viewer interest and an appropriate closing shot to \"reward\" the viewer for staying with you throughout.&nbsp; Keep a good pace and think visual variety. Good luck and have fun with this final \"self-assigned\" photo challenge!</p>',17,7,NULL,'2015-04-13 13:26:39','2015-04-13 13:29:42'),(128,221,'Photography Mentorship Stage 1','','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">This first assignment will help you step out of your \"comfort zone\" and start you looking more closely at subjects and how best to show them off.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Using the techniques I\'ve described for this first \"lesson\" to emphasize subjects within compositions, create a mix of 12 photographs whereby subjects are emphasized through the application of these techniques and others you might discover yourself, along the way.<br /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">I look forward to seeing what you come up with.<br 