c','landscape','','',''),(1056,18,206,'Lesson','','',9,'Gina_09-2.jpg','image/jpeg',391314,'2015-05-10 11:14:55',NULL,'2015-05-10 11:14:58','2015-05-10 11:14:58','c','landscape','','',''),(1057,18,206,'Lesson','','',10,'Gina_10-2.jpg','image/jpeg',247246,'2015-05-10 11:15:26',NULL,'2015-05-10 11:15:28','2015-05-10 11:15:28','c','landscape','','',''),(1058,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Detailed shots','Hi David, thanks for your feedback. To address some of your feedback I have uploaded a couple of images more. I got some detailed shot, although I thought about one of the hand and color coming out of the spray, I must admit I was scared about the lens ;-) I probably have to bring a 200mm next time to try it from afar. It should be cool to get some closeup.',1,'U_1_01.jpg','image/jpeg',246454,'2015-05-12 08:35:38',NULL,'2015-05-12 08:35:40','2015-05-12 08:35:40','c','landscape','','',''),(1059,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Additional shots','Hi David, Here is a (slightly more) closeup of the artist while preparing. I am not really happy with the image, but it was the only chance I got to get such a shot...',2,'U_1_02.jpg','image/jpeg',463232,'2015-05-12 08:37:17',NULL,'2015-05-12 08:37:19','2015-05-12 08:37:19','c','landscape','','',''),(1060,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Additional detailed shot','This is an additional shot of spray cans (to get different colors)... Also not \"that\" happy about this one. In my opinion is missing something, but I cannot pinpoint exactly what...\r\n',3,'U_1_03.jpg','image/jpeg',90597,'2015-05-12 08:38:58',NULL,'2015-05-12 08:38:59','2015-05-12 08:38:59','c','portrait','','',''),(1061,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Greeting','And a last shot I got of the artist...',4,'U_1_04.jpg','image/jpeg',82430,'2015-05-12 08:40:53',NULL,'2015-05-12 08:40:54','2015-05-12 08:40:54','c','portrait','','',''),(1062,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Artist preparation','Another shot of the artist preparing himself and choosing the color...',5,'U_1_05.jpg','image/jpeg',137509,'2015-05-12 08:42:22',NULL,'2015-05-12 08:42:24','2015-05-12 08:42:24','c','landscape','','',''),(1063,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Strong angle modified','Hallo David, as you mentioned in your comment, I tried to crop the image a bit more (although I don\'t like much cropping) and burned an angle to draw attention to the artist. What do you think? Is this what you meant?',6,'U_1_06.jpg','image/jpeg',150632,'2015-05-12 08:43:36',NULL,'2015-05-12 08:43:38','2015-05-12 08:43:38','c','landscape','','',''),(1064,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Starting the painting','I got this image from below with a wide angle to try to get a more dramatic and dynamic effect. I didn\'t do a lot of post processing, except some dodging and burning. I got the sun in the frame to add some interesting light in the image.',7,'U_1_07.jpg','image/jpeg',76547,'2015-05-12 08:44:58',NULL,'2015-05-12 08:44:59','2015-05-12 08:44:59','c','portrait','','',''),(1065,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Paint','I tried to get a different angle, putting in focus the paint and out of focus the painter. The pain bucket is not completely in the frame, and that could be a problem, although it seems to work (but I would try next time to get it all in the frame). Same reasoning go for the feet of the painter. They should be probably be in the frame too. I also tried to use a different angle to add some dynamics to the image. Is it generally speaking a bad idea? My question is if such an image work or not :-)',8,'U_1_08.jpg','image/jpeg',107968,'2015-05-12 08:50:10',NULL,'2015-05-12 08:50:11','2015-05-12 08:50:11','c','landscape','','',''),(1066,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Concentration','When I set to get images, I tried to imagine what I wanted to capture. Concentration of the artists was one of the things I wanted in one or more images. This is the result of trying to do that. The two artists (one out of focus in the background) are very deeply absorbed by their work.',9,'U_1_09.jpg','image/jpeg',134286,'2015-05-12 08:51:53',NULL,'2015-05-12 08:51:54','2015-05-12 08:51:54','c','landscape','','',''),(1067,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','A step back','Every now and then the artist would step back to check from afar how the lions were. I tried to capture those movement and dynamics during the artistic process. I tried to get both the lion and the artist in the frame to give a context to the viewer.',10,'U_1_10.jpg','image/jpeg',152688,'2015-05-12 08:53:18',NULL,'2015-05-12 08:53:20','2015-05-12 08:53:20','c','landscape','','',''),(1068,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Energy','I also wanted to get the energy of spray painting in some frames. Therefore I tried to get images when the artist was deeply involved in the artistic creation process and moved relatively fast between different part of the image. I also liked the idea of putting some of the people walking by to give the viewer a context of urban art (opposed to studio work).',11,'U_1_11.jpg','image/jpeg',134416,'2015-05-12 08:54:42',NULL,'2015-05-12 08:54:44','2015-05-12 08:54:44','c','landscape','','',''),(1069,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Starting from scratch','I like the idea of taking an image when the artist was starting, and I planned to get some images with low shutter speed to get some arm movement (since spray painting have relatively wide arm movements). I wanted really to get the idea that they were starting from nothing.I usually don\'t crop much (if at all) but here there is the white part at the top that maybe could be eliminated. Bad idea?',12,'U_1_12.jpg','image/jpeg',117239,'2015-05-12 08:56:14',NULL,'2015-05-12 08:56:16','2015-05-12 08:56:16','c','landscape','','',''),(1070,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Concentration and energy','I tried to use a different angle (from relatively low and not parallel to the floor) to get a moment of movement and concentration. The artist is concentrated on the printed image that he is copying and at the same time is putting the first draft lines on the wall.',13,'U_1_13.jpg','image/jpeg',116706,'2015-05-12 08:57:38',NULL,'2015-05-12 08:57:39','2015-05-12 08:57:39','c','landscape','','',''),(1071,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Strong angle','I experimented with a different angle and tried to put the relevant piece of information in the frame: art, spray bottles, street and artist, and added a strange angle to give it some movement.',14,'U_1_14.jpg','image/jpeg',146864,'2015-05-12 08:59:03',NULL,'2015-05-12 08:59:04','2015-05-12 08:59:04','c','landscape','','',''),(1072,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Last details','I tried to get an image with low shutter speed of the artist right in front of the lion. Unfortunately the shoes are not 100% in the frame. They should probably be, but everything happened rather fast and I didn\'t notice that immediately. I think that the slightly out of focus artist is kind of nice, but I am not sure if this work really well or not.',15,'U_1_15.jpg','image/jpeg',142970,'2015-05-12 09:00:56',NULL,'2015-05-12 09:00:58','2015-05-12 09:00:58','c','landscape','','',''),(1073,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Power','Hi tried to get some images that would give an idea of power and strength. I tried this image with the sun in the background.',16,'U_1_16.jpg','image/jpeg',91874,'2015-05-12 09:02:16',NULL,'2015-05-12 09:02:17','2015-05-12 09:02:17','c','landscape','','',''),(1074,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Discussing','The two artists were discussing often on how to get the result they wanted. I found it fascinating and therefore I tried to get some shots of the discussion and the wall to give (again) some context for the viewer.',17,'U_1_17.jpg','image/jpeg',103063,'2015-05-12 09:03:31',NULL,'2015-05-12 09:03:32','2015-05-12 09:03:32','c','landscape','','',''),(1075,106,30,'AssignmentSubmission','Close up','I usually don\'t like really close up (if they are not portrait) since they don\'t give much of a context. But I thought I could post one here to get your feedback.',18,'U_1_18.jpg','image/jpeg',126487,'2015-05-12 09:05:08',NULL,'2015-05-12 09:05:09','2015-05-12 09:05:09','c','landscape','','',''),(1076,106,31,'AssignmentSubmission','Wide angle scene 1','In this shot I tried to highlight people and the street. It should be clear who the artist is by the fact that he is holding a spray can. This shot should give enough context to the viewer to understand what is going on and where the artists are working.',1,'U_2_01.jpg','image/jpeg',127419,'2015-05-20 16:00:59',NULL,'2015-05-20 16:01:00','2015-05-20 16:01:00','c','landscape','','',''),(1077,106,31,'AssignmentSubmission','Wide angle scene 2','I came back and try to get wide angle shots. I must admin those are (for me) the most difficult to get. But I tried to include as much context as possible (the city, the street, people, etc.). I tried different things. This shot has the street and the two artists. I like it since it has some kind of \"abstract\" feeling to it, similar to the paintings themselves. Unfortunately people are missing, and they are also a part of the context here.',2,'U_2_02.jpg','image/jpeg',98597,'2015-05-20 16:03:39',NULL,'2015-05-20 16:03:40','2015-05-20 16:03:40','c','landscape','','',''),(1078,106,31,'AssignmentSubmission','Middle distance shot 1','You know already this shot, so not much to comment here. It gives quite a good idea of the artist and his work.',3,'U_2_03.jpg','image/jpeg',126487,'2015-05-20 16:05:16',NULL,'2015-05-20 16:05:17','2015-05-20 16:05:17','c','landscape','','',''),(1079,106,31,'AssignmentSubmission','Middle distance shot 2','I like this shot as it is a \"moment captured\". It gives to the reader a view in the moment. What the artist was doing. It contains elements like spray cans, drawings, wall with the result of the work and the street (context). I kind of like it since it has some \"life\" in it, instead of looking \"still\"...',4,'U_2_04.jpg','image/jpeg',128608,'2015-05-20 16:06:51',NULL,'2015-05-20 16:06:52','2015-05-20 16:06:52','c','landscape','','',''),(1080,106,31,'AssignmentSubmission','Middle distance shot 3','In this shot the green of the trees in the background gives the viewer a clear indication that the artist was working in the open, on the street. The out of focus people gives and additional indication that the story is taking place on the street (although I am asking myself if the position of the people could be better).',5,'U_2_05.jpg','image/jpeg',87960,'2015-05-20 16:07:58',NULL,'2015-05-20 16:07:59','2015-05-20 16:07:59','c','portrait','','',''),(1081,106,31,'AssignmentSubmission','Middle distance shot 4','You know this shot too, so not too much to comment here. We already discussed it ;-)',6,'U_2_06.jpg','image/jpeg',134416,'2015-05-20 16:09:06',NULL,'2015-05-20 16:09:08','2015-05-20 16:09:08','c','landscape','','',''),(1082,106,31,'AssignmentSubmission','Middle distance shot 5','There are things in this shot I like and things I don\'t. I like the fact that he is shielding from the sun, giving the reader an indication that painting in this condition are not easy (since is in the open). What I don\'t like (but I don\'t find horrible either) is the fact that the arm and the spray can are not 100% in the frame. They should probably be in the frame for the photo to be \"ok\". On the other side I kind of like the fact that they are on the border of the image, that they are like \"hints\". They are not the focus of the shot, they just give \"slightly\" some context to the image. This is why I kind of like it in this way. What do you think?',7,'U_2_07.jpg','image/jpeg',106688,'2015-05-20 16:10:16',NULL,'2015-05-20 16:10:17','2015-05-20 16:10:17','c','landscape','','',''),(1083,106,31,'AssignmentSubmission','Portrait Shot 1','I know you did not ask for portraits, but I thought I might add a couple that I think gives an idea of the power and energy that those artists transmits. What do you think?',8,'U_2_08.jpg','image/jpeg',73221,'2015-05-20 16:11:25',NULL,'2015-05-20 16:11:26','2015-05-20 16:11:26','c','landscape','','',''),(1084,106,31,'AssignmentSubmission','Portrait shot 2','Here is an other portrait that should give an idea of the environment the artist is working in. Mask, spray cans, without shirts since is hot. I think it transmits energy and gives the reader indications of what the artist is going through, of his work.',9,'U_2_09.jpg','image/jpeg',82368,'2015-05-20 16:12:47',NULL,'2015-05-20 16:12:49','2015-05-20 16:12:49','c','portrait','','',''),(1085,106,31,'AssignmentSubmission','Close up shot 1','A close-up of a dirty hand holding a spray can, while working. The only thing I don\'t like is the paper, since it would probably not be so clear for the viewer what this is. What do you think?',10,'U_2_10.jpg','image/jpeg',133523,'2015-05-20 16:13:57',NULL,'2015-05-20 16:13:59','2015-05-20 16:13:59','c','landscape','','',''),(1086,106,31,'AssignmentSubmission','Close up shot 2','A shot as you suggested, a hand picking a spray can. Although I am not 100% sure the composition works so well (for the feet), or maybe they let the viewer understand how the artist is picking cans (standing)...',11,'U_2_11.jpg','image/jpeg',131919,'2015-05-20 16:15:00',NULL,'2015-05-20 16:15:02','2015-05-20 16:15:02','c','landscape','','',''),(1087,106,31,'AssignmentSubmission','','I tried something different, doing a close-up adding some movements with a slow shutter speed. The spray can is easily recognisable so the movement should add some energy to the image, although I am not really satisfied with the background. What do you think? Does such an image work at all? Or not at all?',12,'U_2_12.jpg','image/jpeg',337417,'2015-05-20 16:16:27',NULL,'2015-05-20 16:16:29','2015-05-20 16:16:29','c','landscape','','',''),(1088,112,32,'AssignmentSubmission','San Diego Velodrome','Pic #1 - Stop Motion Tv - 1/1000 sec. Av - F10 ISO 400',1,'S_2_01.jpg','image/jpeg',123828,'2015-05-21 05:52:36',NULL,'2015-05-21 05:52:37','2015-05-21 05:52:37','c','landscape','','',''),(1089,112,32,