8,'The Photo Essay','<p>Self-assignments are an excellent way to build your portfolio, gain hands-on experience and show prospective employers that - you can do it! If you\'ve always wanted to try a self-commissioned project - or have attempted them in the past without success, this online photography course will bring you stunningly through it and set you up for more.&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Includes Skype Consultation with Instructor.</strong></span></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Many photographers know the value of self-assigned work. Yet commissioning oneself to do a project requires good planning, discipline and a clear vision of what is to be achieved. Once complete and in your portfolio, creatively-executed, self-assigned bodies of work speak volumes of your ability to develop ideas and deliver them in a stunning and professional way. Whether your aim is to land that first assignment or you simply want to expand your horizons as a visual storyteller, this interactive online photography course gives you the skill-set and mentorship to - make it happen.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Upon completion of this course, you will be able to:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Select stories that capture, inform and motivate audiences</li>\r\n<li>Plan a photo-essay project from start to finish</li>\r\n<li>Make contacts and establish rapport to get the story coverage you need</li>\r\n<li>Effectively edit your work</li>\r\n<li>Target appropriate markets for sales</li>\r\n<li>Submit a polished and professional photo essay for editorial consideration</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>What you will need:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Digital SLR or compact mirrorless camera (film is also fine, but you\'ll need to scan images for upload to the TCI website)</li>\r\n<li>Selection of lenses ranging from wide-angle to medium telephoto</li>\r\n<li>Computer with photo-processing software (e.g. Photoshop)</li>\r\n<li>A light, but study tripod 